    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Discipline in which chemistry, physics, and mathematics are combined with basic engineering principles to solve environmental, biomedical, societal, or technological problems arising in the application of chemistry.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000032741/Peterson's Guide to Graduate and Professional Programs (1967-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Disciplina en que la química, física y matemáticas son combinadas con los principios básicos de la ingeniería para resolver problemas ambientales, biomédicos, sociales o tecnológicos originados en la aplicación de la química.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Spanish</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000131/CDBP-SNPC</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000051034/TAA database (2000-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Vakgebied waarin scheikunde, natuurkunde en wiskunde zijn gecombineerd met de beginselen van de techniek om milieu-, biomedische, maatschappelijke of technische problemen op te lossen, die ontstaan bij die toepassing van scheikunde.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
